# .cursorrules — OHM Playwright Automation

## Project Context
This is a Playwright UI test automation suite for **Lumen OHM** (Online Homework Manager).
- Staging environment: https://ohm-stg.preprod.ludev.team/
- Production smoke tests are a separate suite — do not mix them here
- Application under test is an instructor-facing LMS tool built on a web platform

## Stack
- Framework: Playwright (TypeScript)
- Test runner: `@playwright/test`
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode preferred)
- Node version: 18+

## File & Folder Structure
```
/tests
  /specs          ← Markdown test case source files (human-readable)
  /e2e            ← Playwright test files (*.spec.ts)
    /auth
    /home
    /course-creation
    /gradebook
    /admin
    /utilities
  /pages          ← Page Object Model classes (*.page.ts)
  /fixtures       ← Test data files (*.json or *.ts)
  /helpers        ← Shared utilities and setup helpers
playwright.config.ts
.env.example
```

## Coding Conventions

### Always use Page Object Model (POM)
- Each major page or feature area gets its own Page Object class in `/tests/pages/`
- Page Objects expose semantic methods, not raw locators: `loginPage.loginAs(user)` not `page.fill('#username', ...)`
- Example:
```ts
// tests/pages/login.page.ts
export class LoginPage {
  constructor(private page: Page) {}
  async loginAs(username: string, password: string) { ... }
  async clickForgotPassword() { ... }
}
```

### Locator Priority (in order of preference)
1. `data-testid` attributes — most stable, prefer these
2. ARIA roles: `getByRole('button', { name: /submit/i })`
3. Labels: `getByLabel(/email/i)`
4. Text: `getByText(...)` — use sparingly, avoid for dynamic content
5. CSS selectors — last resort only

### Environment Variables
- Never hardcode credentials or URLs
- All environment-specific values go in `.env` (gitignored)
- Document required vars in `.env.example`
```
BASE_URL=https://ohm-stg.preprod.ludev.team
OHM_USERNAME=
OHM_PASSWORD=
OHM_ADMIN_USERNAME=
OHM_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
TEST_COURSE_ID=
TEST_ENROLLMENT_KEY=
```

### Test Structure
- One `test.describe` block per spec section (matching the spec number in ohm-test-suite.md)
- Test IDs in names should match spec IDs: `'1.1 — Confirm login...'`
- Use `test.beforeEach` for authentication where needed
- Use `test.use({ storageState })` with saved auth state to avoid logging in for every test

### Authentication
- Create a `tests/helpers/auth.setup.ts` that logs in and saves storage state
- Reference it in `playwright.config.ts` as a project dependency
- This prevents re-login on every test and speeds up the suite significantly

### Risk Levels
- Tag tests with risk level using Playwright tags:
```ts
test('1.1 — Login @high', ...)
test('2.2 — Add New Course @medium', ...)
```
- Run only high-risk tests: `npx playwright test --grep @high`

### Assertions
- Always use `expect(...).toBeVisible()` over checking for element existence
- Use `expect(...).toHaveURL(...)` after navigation
- Add meaningful error context where possible
- Wait for network idle or specific element visibility instead of arbitrary timeouts

### New Tab / Popup Handling
```ts
const [newPage] = await Promise.all([
  context.waitForEvent('page'),
  page.getByRole('link', { name: /link text/i }).click(),
]);
await newPage.waitForLoadState();
expect(newPage.url()).toContain('expected-domain.com');
```

## Generating New Test Files
When asked to generate a test file:
1. Reference the corresponding section in `tests/specs/ohm-test-suite.md`
2. Create or reuse the Page Object for that area
3. Follow the naming convention: `[feature-area].spec.ts`
4. Include all test cases from the spec section, even if implementation is `test.skip()`
5. Add a comment at the top linking back to the spec section number

## Known Caveats & Notes from the Spec
- **User Settings**: Accessibility/Display Preferences are changing in an upcoming sprint — tests for those should be skipped/marked pending
- **Admin breadcrumb**: Groups page missing breadcrumb dashboard — known bug, don't assert for it
- **New Instructors Report**: Best tested in Production only — skip in staging suite or mark as `@production-only`
- **Gradebook status flags**: Require specific student data states (IP, OT, PT, etc.) — use seeded test data
- **Desmos**: Requires its own dedicated test section — placeholder tests only for now
- **Debug Mode** (Utilities 19.10): Do not automate; mark as `test.skip()`
- **Update ExtRefs** (Utilities 19.15): Marked as dangerous in spec — do not automate
- **LMS Integration** (Due Dates, Copies of Copies): Requires Canvas LMS setup — separate suite

## When Generating Tests, Always Ask About
- What test user roles are available (instructor, admin, student)?
- Are there seeded courses or should the test create its own data?
- Should tests clean up after themselves (delete created courses, users, etc.)?
